<!--112-->Morgul Gates x4<br />
<!--100-->All Blades Perish x2    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">19 companions! Seems way too much but think for a second. Getting them out quickly is important to allow you to double move. Everyone except Frodo (and maybe Boromir) is expendable. Even better the spare copies can be used to heal injured companions. All the weapons can go on the cart from the start. You have no companions, no conditions and only 2 events so many of your opponents cards will be wasted. How many fellowship cards will clog your hand each turn - oh thats right, none! You can play all of your fellowship cards every turn. <br />
<br />
You need to bid big to go first and get out the cart. Don&#39;t worry about the burdens, Sam will be along soon and remove them.<br />
<br />
Easy to play but one tip is keep Borimir alive, believe it or not he is the second most important companion because his special ability is what keeps Frodo alive.<br />
<br />
Shadow is also easy. Tons of minions combined with a fast flow of fellowship cards ensures that you will always have lots of minions to put down. Gates make your guys affordable. There are no tricky combos here, everything you get you can play as long as you can afford it. Cantea is the best minion you have as he destroys those annoying Flaming Brands. If your area has lots of archer decks swap the All Blades Perish for Relentless Charges. <br />
<br />
Now go and find the ring. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
